settings.description: The destroyed constructions were destroyed by the boss bass before the level,enjoy.
You sneak into Boom Boom's Japanese castle in Kyoto like an cool guy, and you have to defeat him!
Sometimes you have to wonder... where DO all these jumping and fire breathing statues come from? well... here's the answer.
Ice, munchers, flurries, penguins, and... shoes?! seems like this wild combo is something that's a bit toooo chill to exist, but it does!
Actually it's not too much of a panic, for this level's not tooooo difficult for one! yeah, good ol Chuck might try to get in your way, but that's all for the dangers here!
a whole castle filled with bricks that can be turned into koopas and mushrooms? what a dream! course, Bowser's waiting at the end to ruin the fun!
with a boatload of bullets! honestly love how the four way bullet bill generators exist, for they're such an underused feature found originally in super mario world.
I'm so bored to put the description :v,enjoy.
I was thinking that would be MORE hard,the random Boom-Boom is because he was rebuilding his fortress,enjoy.
Try and get the mushroom to the end!
